vyLGSc1kHJI.title: Real Madrid vs Athletic Bilbao 08/05/10 5 - 1 (HD)
vyLGSc1kHJI.description:
C.Ronaldo 22' (PK) 1-0
F.J.Yeste 41' 1-1
G.Higuain 73' 2-1
S.Ramos 80' 3-1
K.Benzema 81' 4-1
Marcelo 89' 5-1

Stadium:    Estadio Santiago Bernabéu, Spain
Attendance: 80,000
Match Time: May 8, 2010, 20:00 UK
Official(s): César Muñiz Fernández (Referee)

Cristiano Ronaldo and Gonzalo Higuain were again on the scoresheet as Real Madrid ensured the Primera Division title race would go to the final week with an ultimately convincing 5-1 victory over 10-man Athletic Bilbao.

The duo had netted 51 league goals between them in 56 games prior to this fixture and they were on the mark once more as Madrid stayed within a point of leaders Barcelona, who beat Sevilla 3-2.

Ronaldo, who struck his first hat-trick for Madrid in Wednesday's 4-1 win over Real Mallorca, opened the scoring from the penalty spot in the 22nd minute in an incident that also saw Athletic defender Fernando Amorebieta sent-off.

Athletic captain Fran Yeste threatened to ruin Madrid's night when he scored a brilliant equaliser just before half-time, but four goals in the final 17 minutes from Higuain, Sergio Ramos, Karim Benzema and Marcelo earned the home side their 18th win in their last 19 league games.

Manuel Pellegrini's side are still underdogs to win the title however, as Barca are at home to lowly Real Valladolid next weekend while Madrid go to Malaga.

Athletic striker Gaizka Toquero gave the home side a couple of scares early on, bringing a diving save out of Iker Casillas with a flicked header and then racing through on goal after robbing Raul Albiol only to slice wide.

Aside from those incidents though it was almost all Madrid, with Ronaldo twice going close before finding it third time lucky after the home side were awarded a penalty in the 20th minute.

Higuain's shot from the edge of the box struck Amorebieta's hand and not only did referee Cesar Muniz Fernandez award a penalty but he also dismissed the Athletic centre-back.

It looked harsh to give both the penalty and a red card, and Ronaldo added salt to Athletic's wounds by calmly rolling in the resulting penalty for his 26th goal of the season. After that it was only the goalkeeping of Gorka Iraizoz that kept Madrid from running away with the game as he denied Higuain twice and also Fernando Gago and Esteban Granero in quick succession.

A second Madrid goal looked inevitable, but it was actually Athletic who found the back of the next as they stunned the Bernabeu with a superb equaliser from Yeste.

There appeared little danger when the Athletic captain picked the ball up with plenty of Madrid defenders back, but he danced inside Sergio Ramos, Gago, Xabi Alonso and Albiol before driving a low shot past Casillas.

That was a huge blow for Madrid, and Pellegrini responded by sending on Kaka for Gago at the break.

The second period continued in a similar vein to the first, with Madrid virtually camped in the Athletic half.

Ronaldo, Kaka and Marcelo all went close with headers while Granero's 20-yard strike clipped the top of the crossbar.

But with half-an-hour to go the title was heading to Barca, and Athletic almost hammered another nail in Madrid's coffin when Yeste went close with a shot that Casillas saved with his feet.

The final 25 minutes saw Madrid laying siege to the visiting goal.

Higuain was proving the biggest threat and he went close three times before finally putting Madrid back in front.

News had filtered through to the Bernabeu that Sevilla had trimmed Barca's lead from 3-0 to 3-2 and Madrid responded almost immediately to give the home fans further reason for optimism.

Alonso's free-kick was deflected goalwards off an Athletic defender, and although Iraizoz did well to palm the ball away, Higuain was perfectly placed beyond the far post to head in his 27th of the season.

That was the breakthrough Madrid needed and they added three more goals through Ramos, Benzema and Marcelo late on to seal their 10th home win in 11 meetings with Athletic and keep the title race going to the wire.

drGr0W7JHys.title: Подарочный американский легкий танк второго уровня T1E6
drGr0W7JHys.description:
24 декабря разработчики игры World of Tanks преподнесли игрокам новогодний подарок - американский легкий танк второго уровня T1E6. Посмотрим, как ведет себя эта машина в бою и на что она способна.

Танк T1E6 получился неплох. Его достоинства: скорострельная пушка с кассетой на 5 выстрелов, небольшие размеры, хорошая скорость. Из недостатков: небольшие значения пробития и урона, большой разброс и длительное сведение пушки; малый боекомплект, небольшая дальность стрельбы и слабое бронирование. Танк T1E6 ориентирован на ближний бой, так как на дельней и средней дистанции толку от него мало.

Мастерский бой на американском легком танке второго уровня T1E6 - http://youtu.be/kKwvvNHpYVY

r-NGlTvNlyk.title: Neena Gupta
r-NGlTvNlyk.description:
Neena Gupta (born 4 July 1959) is an Indian film and television actress and director-producer. She won the 1994 National Film Award for Best Supporting Actress for Woh Chokri. She is a popular actress in Indian commercial cinema, but it is her work with art filmmakers of India, like Shyam Benegal that got her recognition as an actress of considerable repute. She also hosted the Indian version of the television quiz show The Weakest Link, Kamzor Kadii Kaun.Gupta has made appearances in several international films, such as Gandhi (1982), in which she played the niece of the Mahatma Gandhi, and the Merchant Ivory films The Deceivers (1988), In Custody (1993), and Cotton Mary (1999).
She starred along with Madhuri Dixit in Khalnayak (1993); she was featured in the popular song "Choli ke peeche" in the movie. She has made the telefilms Lajwanti and Bazar Sitaram (1993), which won the 1993 National Film Award for Best First Non-Feature Film.
Her big break on television came with Khandaan (1985), Gulzar's Mirza Ghalib (1987), a TV miniseries, followed by Shyam Benegal's Bharat Ek Khoj (1988) and later Dard (1994 DD Metro), Gumraah (1995 DD Metro), Saans (Star Plus), Saat Phere (2005), Chitthi (2003), Meri Biwi Ka Jawab Nahin (2004), and Kitani Mohabbat Hai (2009).
She also hosted the Indian version of the TV series The Weakest Link, Kamzor Kadii Kaun (Star Plus), and appeared in Jassi Jaissi Koi Nahin (Sony TV), which gave her considerable popularity.
She has directed successful TV series, such as Saans (1999), Ans Siski in (2000) and Kyun Hota Hai Pyarrr. She played the role of Shubha, one of the four women main leads in Ladies Special, a daily soap on Sony TV. She is now seen in Dil se Diya Vachan as Doctor by profession & mother-in-law of the lead character Nandani aired on Zee TV from Monday to Friday at 7pm.
She also ran a theater production company, 'Sahaj Productions' with actor, Rajendra Gupta, and acted and produced Hindi play Soorya Ki Antim Kiran Se Soorya Ki Paheli Kiran Tak.
She has also had some roles in Rishtey which was aired on Zee TV during 1999-2000.

Source : http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neena_Gupta & Google image.

eGjkYB2IASU.title: Apple Cider DIY for Your Halloween Party or Harry Potter Lifestyle - Holly Hobby
eGjkYB2IASU.description:
How to make cider using regular apple juice - perfect for a Halloween party!  Add rum for a Halloween cocktail.  Stay for more http://bit.ly/HollyHobby  
This apple cider recipe isn't 100% homemade, since we bought the apple juice from the store, but adding all of the holiday spices really brings it to the next level.  Holly and Hilary served this cider at last year's Halloween party and had to make three batches to keep up with demand!  

Here are the ingredients for the cider: 
1/2 Gallon of Unsweetened Apple Juice
1 Orange 
15 Cloves (count 'em out)
15 Allspice berries
4 Sticks of Cinnamon (can be used for garnish later!)
1 Teaspoon of Nutmeg
7 Pods of Cardamon 
1 cup (or more) of Spiced Rum per batch if you're making the cocktail version

Tools You'll Need: 
A 3-quart saucepan and stove
A strainer 
Ice if you need to cool down the batch before adding Rum.  

If you're making the non-alcoholic version, you don't need to cool it down before serving unless you're concerned for your safety.  

Since alcohol is burned off at near-boiling temperatures, we used the ice to quickly cool it before adding the rum for max impact.  (Thanks to Lizzy for that idea!!)

To actually make the cider, pour the apple juice into the saucepan and bring to a boil.  

Once it's boiling, you can add all of the Halloween spices and the orange cut into quarters.  

Bring the cider down to simmering, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes.  

If you're making the non-alcoholic version, just strain and serve the cider with a cinnamon stick.  

If you want to add rum, cool the batch down in some ice water, strain, and serve!

This recipe was adapted from one on Simply Recipes: http://www.simplyrecipes.com/recipes/hot_mulled_cider/

My friend Hilary works for Polaris, the gaming network in Maker Studios!  If you have a channel and would like to work with her and others on the Maker team, you can apply here: http://awe.sm/bKBD7

Maker also gives me access to awesome royalty free music from audiomicro.com and Epidemic Sound.
